# Data Layer Rules

## Imports
- ❌ NO imports from another feature's `data/` layer
- ❌ NO analytics imports — analytics belongs exclusively in domain UseCases
- ✅ May import own feature's `domain/` (entities, repository contracts)
- ✅ May import `core/` (error, api, storage, network)

## File naming and structure
Files must be prefixed with the feature name:
- ✅ `user_config_repository_impl.dart`, `user_config_local_data_source.dart`, `routes_route_model.dart`
- ❌ `repository_impl.dart`, `local_data_source.dart`, `route_model.dart`

Data layer folder layout:
```
data/
  datasource/   ← local & remote data sources
  models/       ← JSON models (see model-entity-separation.mdc)
  repository/   ← repository implementations
```

Models MUST NOT be imported by domain or presentation. Only the repository uses them.
See `model-entity-separation.mdc` for the full model/entity rule.

## Exception → Failure conversion
All exceptions MUST be caught at the **repository implementation** level and converted to `Failure`.
Data sources may throw — the repository catches and maps.

Use the `ExceptionX.toFailure(source:)` extension from `core/error/exception_x.dart`.
It automatically maps `ApiException` → `Failure.api`, `FormatException`/`TypeError` → `Failure.parse`, everything else → `Failure.base`.
Never construct `Failure.*` variants manually in a catch block.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — user_config repository impl
@LazySingleton(as: UserConfigRepository)
class UserConfigRepositoryImpl implements UserConfigRepository {
  final UserConfigLocalDataSource _local;
  UserConfigRepositoryImpl(this._local);

  @override
  FutureEither<AppThemeMode?> getAppThemeMode() async {
    try {
      final raw = await _local.getUserConfig(key: UserConfigConsts.themeKey);
      final mode = raw != null ? AppThemeMode.values.byName(raw) : null;
      return Right(mode);
    } on Exception catch (e) {
      return Left(e.toFailure(source: '$runtimeType'));
    }
  }

  @override
  FutureEither<void> setTheme(AppThemeMode themeMode) async {
    try {
      await _local.setUserConfig(key: UserConfigConsts.themeKey, value: themeMode.name);
      return const Right(null);
    } on Exception catch (e) {
      return Left(e.toFailure(source: '$runtimeType'));
    }
  }
}

// ❌ BAD — manually constructing Failure variants
} catch (e) {
  return Left(Failure.base(source: '$runtimeType', message: e.toString()));
}

// ❌ BAD — exception thrown in data source escapes to domain/BLoC
void _ensureSupportedValue(Object? value) {
  if (value is! String && value is! int) {
    throw Exception('Unsupported type'); // raw exception, never caught
  }
}
```

## Storage — LocalStorage vs SecureStorage
Two distinct abstractions exist in `core/storage/`. Choose based on sensitivity:

| Abstraction | Class | Use for |
|-------------|-------|---------|
| `LocalStorage` | `lib/src/core/storage/local_storage/local_storage.dart` | Non-sensitive preferences (theme, locale, onboarding flags) |
| `SecureStorage` | `lib/src/core/storage/secure_storage/secure_storage.dart` | Sensitive data (auth tokens, credentials, keys) |

Both share the same interface (`read`, `write`, `delete`, `deleteAll`, `containsKey`, `readAll`). Inject by type — never use `SharedPreferences` or `FlutterSecureStorage` directly in a data source.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — non-sensitive user preference
@LazySingleton()
class UserConfigLocalDataSourceImpl implements UserConfigLocalDataSource {
  final LocalStorage _storage;
  UserConfigLocalDataSourceImpl(this._storage);
  ...
}

// ✅ GOOD — auth token
@LazySingleton()
class AuthLocalDataSourceImpl implements AuthLocalDataSource {
  final SecureStorage _storage;
  AuthLocalDataSourceImpl(this._storage);
  ...
}

// ❌ BAD — direct platform dependency
final prefs = await SharedPreferences.getInstance();
```

## Cancel tokens
For slow or user-interruptible requests, add `ApiCancelToken?` to data source and repository methods.
See `cancel-token.mdc` for the full data source → repository → UseCase Params → BLoC flow.

## API usage
- Use `ApiClient` for all HTTP calls — follow `lib/src/core/api/usage_documentation.md`
- ❌ Never import `Dio` / `http` directly in a repository or data source

## No analytics
- ❌ Never call `Analytics.track(...)` anywhere in the data layer
- ❌ Never import `core/monitoring/analytics/` in data layer files
